    <Container isError={!!error} onClick={handleClick} ref={containerRef}>
      <TagsInput
        value={formatValue(value)}
        onChange={onChange}
        name={name}
        onBlur={handleBlur}
        placeHolder={placeholder}
        onInputBlur={handleInputBlur}
      />
    </Container>
  </FormField>
);
```

Here, we are using a `useEffect()` hook to access the container element and the input element of the `<TagsInput>` component. We are then adding an event listener to the container element to listen for the Enter key press and prevent form submission if the input element is focused.

